Therefore, beta-HCG is the most likely tumor marker to be elevated in this patient. Carcinoembryonic antigen is a tumor marker for colorectal cancer, pancreatic cancer, and breast cancer. Prostate-specific antigen is a tumor marker for prostate cancer. Placental alkaline phosphatase is a tumor marker for germ cell tumors of the ovary and testis.
